x4freetext: Isospin and strong coupling effects in neutron
Enriched, metallic powder in polyethylene cylinders,
25 millim. inner diam., 50 millim. long, 0.5 millim.
The detector efficiency determined by two methods,
by detection of neutrons from D(d,n)He-3 at different
angles, and by elastic scattering on hydrogen.
For dimension of sample and multiple scattering.
Absolute cross sections are given with an
overall uncertainty varying between 7 and 20% including
The overall accuracy in flux measurements
The absolute neutron detector efficiency was
estimated to have an uncertainty of 5%.
